modules.description: This module encodes and decodes sequences of integers into compact 63-bit representations, using a format derived from the Simple-8b encoding. It operates on `int` values within the range 0 to 5.8e17, producing encoded output as sequences, bigarrays, or writing directly to output channels. Concrete use cases include compressing large sequences of integers for storage or transmission, and efficiently decoding such sequences from files or streams.
